The paper deals with robot planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper involves using data-driven imitation learning to train planning policies, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves working with maps and environments, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or systems and control (cs.SY).
